timeline.message: Removed obsolete EARLY-REGISTRATION and LIR-PARTITIONED PI statuses.

Add stricter inetnum status hierarchy.
Enforce on create only initially.
Removed ALLOCATED PI and NOT-SET inetnum statuses.
Remove error messages for does not have status or incorrect status. These situations can never occur anymore.
Add warnings on modify/delete inetnums resulting in invalid status hierarchy.
Seperate stricter hierarchy is not needed as modify and delete don't enforce it anyway.
SUB-ALLOCATED PA under SUB-ALLOCATED PA should be allowed.
Remove test which checks against obsolete legacy SUBTLA status. There are no more objects with this status.
LIR PARTITIONED PA should be allowed under LIR PARTITIONED PA.

timeline.bodyText: Should we still allow LIR-PARTITIONED PA under SUB-ALLOCATED PA (for now)?
timeline.author: eshryane

timeline.bodyText: Should we still allow LIR-PARTITIONED PA under LIR-PARTITIONED PA (for now) ?
timeline.author: eshryane

timeline.message: Allow LIR-PARTITIONED PA/SUB-PARTITIONED PA as child/parent of one another.

timeline.author: eshryane

replies.bodyText: Done, cleaned up left over test code..
replies.author: sbusk

timeline.bodyText: Should this test be removed? It's testing the error message, not the missing status
timeline.author: eshryane

replies.bodyText: It was creating a situation that cannot be created and then checking against (parent has no status). All that logic has been removed as it is no longer possible to create these types of situations and none exist in the data anymore. Test is therefore obsolete.
replies.author: sbusk
